The university made the announcement of an 8% fee increase on Monday, which also applies to its international students. JOHANNESBURG The Higher Education Department says Wits University s decision to increase its fees by 8% next year has come as no surprise.The university made the announcement on Monday, which also applies to its international students.Wits says it had no choice but to hike the fees in order to remain financially sustainable and take in more students in 2017.Earlier this year, Minister Blade Nzimande announced that fees will be capped at 8%.The department s Diane Parker says: There was no fees increase for students last year, however government decided to add an amount to the block grant of funding to universities to subsidise universities generally. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)